ess philosophical, political, and moral issues in her own voice. Her three public orations and almost all of her letters, translated into English, are presented here for the first time.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aAuthors, Latin (Medieval and modern). 0aFedele, Cassandra. 0aFeminists. 0aHumanists. 0aLiterature. 0aSpeeches, addresses, etc., Latin (Medieval and modern). 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / General.2bisacsh1 aKing, Magaret L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRabil, Albert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRobin, Diana.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311063538640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226239330423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226239330.jpg  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles